description.p:
in which:


R1 represents I, a radioactive isotope of I or a group with the formula Sn (R3)3 in which R3 is an alkyl group;


R2 represents H ; an alkyl group in C1 to C6 ; a phenyl group; a phenyl group substituted by a halogen atom, a methyl group or a methoxy group; a phenalkyl or phenylalkenyl group whose alkyl or alkenyl group comprises 1 to 6 carbon atoms and whose phenyl group may be substituted by a halogen atom; a cycloalkyl group in C3 to C8 or an alkynyl group;


X represents H, I, F, Cl, Br, --CH3, --OCH3, --C2 H5, --CF3, --OH, --NH2, --NO2, --CN, --NCS, N3, --NHCOCH3 or --OCOCH3 ; and


Y represents a hydrogen, chlorine, iodine or bromine atom, or the methyl group, provided that X does not represent F or Cl when Y represents H.
